199template <class T>
200class Local {
201 public:
202 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
203 template <class S>
204 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
205 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
211 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
212 }
213
217 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
218
222 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
223
224 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
225
226 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
227
238 template <class S>
239 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
240 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
241 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
242 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
243 if (b == nullptr) return false;
244 return *a == *b;
245 }
246
247 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
248 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
249 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
250 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
251 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
252 if (b == nullptr) return false;
253 return *a == *b;
254 }
255
266 template <class S>
267 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
268 return !operator==(that);
269 }
270
271 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
272 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
273 return !operator==(that);
274 }
275
281 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
282#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
283 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
284 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
285 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
286#endif
287 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
288 }
289
295 template <class S>
296 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
297 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
298 }
299
305 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
306 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
307 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
308 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
309 const BasicTracedReference<T>& that);
310
311 private:
312 friend class TracedReferenceBase;
313 friend class Utils;
314 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
315 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
316 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
317 template<class F> friend class Local;
318 template <class F>
319 friend class MaybeLocal;
320 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
321 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
322 friend class String;
323 friend class Object;
324 friend class Context;
325 friend class Isolate;
326 friend class Private;
327 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
328 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
329 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
330 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
331 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
332 friend class HandleScope;
333 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
334 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
335 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
336 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
337 template <class F>
338 friend class ReturnValue;
339 template <class F>
340 friend class Traced;
341 template <class F>
342 friend class TracedGlobal;
343 template <class F>
344 friend class BasicTracedReference;
345 template <class F>
346 friend class TracedReference;

348 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
349 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
350 T* val_;

371template <class T>
372class MaybeLocal {
373 public:
374 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
375 template <class S>
376 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
377 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
378 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
379 }
380
381 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
382
387 template <class S>
388 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
389 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
390 return !IsEmpty();
391 }
392
397 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
398
403 template <class S>
404 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
405 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
406 }
407
408 private:
409 T* val_;
410};

433static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
434static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
435
436template <typename T>
437class WeakCallbackInfo {
438 public:
439 using Callback = void (*)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
440
441 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
442 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
443 Callback* callback)
444 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
445 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
446 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
447 }
448 }
449
450 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
451 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
452 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
453
454 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
455 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
456 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
457 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
458 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
459 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
460 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
461
462 private:
463 Isolate* isolate_;
464 T* parameter_;
465 Callback* callback_;
466 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
467};
468
469
470// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
471// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
472// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
473// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
474// possible to request a second pass callback.
475enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

490template <class T> class PersistentBase {
491 public:

515 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);

517
518 template <class S>
519 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
520 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
521 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
522 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
523 if (b == nullptr) return false;
524 return *a == *b;
525 }
526
527 template <class S>
528 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
529 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
530 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
531 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
532 if (b == nullptr) return false;
533 return *a == *b;
534 }
535
536 template <class S>
537 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
538 return !operator==(that);

542 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {

615 friend class Object;

618 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);

620 T* val_;

668template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
669 public:
673 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
679 template <class S>
680 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
681 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
682 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
683 }
689 template <class S, class M2>
690 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
691 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
692 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
693 }
700 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
701 Copy(that);
702 }
703 template <class S, class M2>
704 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
705 Copy(that);
706 }
707 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
708 Copy(that);
709 return *this;
710 }
711 template <class S, class M2>
712 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
713 Copy(that);
714 return *this;
715 }
721 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
722 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
723 }
724
725 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
726 template <class S>
727 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) {
728#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
729 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
730 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
731 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
732#endif
733 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
734 }
735
736 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
737 template <class S>
738 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const {
739 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
740 }
741
742 private:
743 friend class Isolate;
744 friend class Utils;
745 template<class F> friend class Local;
746 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
747 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
748
749 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
750 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
751 template<class S, class M2>
752 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
753};

834class TracedReferenceBase {
835 public:

841
846 V8_INLINE void Reset();
847
851 V8_INLINE v8::Local<v8::Value> Get(v8::Isolate* isolate) const;
852
857 bool IsEmptyThreadSafe() const {
858 return this->GetSlotThreadSafe() == nullptr;
859 }
860
864 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
865
870 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
871
872 protected:
876 void SetSlotThreadSafe(void* new_val) {
877 reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<void*>*>(&val_)->store(
878 new_val, std::memory_order_relaxed);
879 }
880
884 const void* GetSlotThreadSafe() const {
885 return reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<const void*> const*>(&val_)->load(
886 std::memory_order_relaxed);
887 }
888
889 V8_EXPORT void CheckValue() const;
890
891 // val_ points to a GlobalHandles node.
892 internal::Address* val_ = nullptr;
893
894 friend class internal::BasicTracedReferenceExtractor;
895 template <typename F>
896 friend class Local;
897 template <typename U>
898 friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&, const Local<U>&);
899 friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&,
900 const TracedReferenceBase&);
901};

1162
1166 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference&& rhs);
1167

1172 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1173
1177 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1178
1182 template <class S>
1183 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1184
1189 template <class S>
1190 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1191
1192 template <class S>
1193 V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1194 return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1195 const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1196 }

1407class ScriptOriginOptions {
1408 public:
1409 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1410 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1411 bool is_module = false)
1412 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1413 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1414 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1415 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1416 : flags_(flags &
1417 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1418
1419 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1420 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1421 }
1422 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1423 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1424 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1425
1426 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1427
1428 private:
1429 enum {
1430 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1431 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1432 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1433 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1434 };
1435 const int flags_;
1436};

1815class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1816 public:
1824 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1825 enum BufferPolicy {
1826 BufferNotOwned,
1827 BufferOwned
1828 };
1829
1830 CachedData()
1831 : data(nullptr),
1832 length(0),
1833 rejected(false),
1834 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1835
1836 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1837 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1838 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1839 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1840 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1841 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1842 ~CachedData();
1843 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1844 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1845 const uint8_t* data;
1846 int length;
1847 bool rejected;
1848 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1849
1850 // Prevent copying.
1851 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1852 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1853 };

1869 // alive.
1870 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;

2421// by the sampling profiler API.
2422struct V8_EXPORT RegisterState {
2423 RegisterState();
2424 ~RegisterState();
2425 RegisterState(const RegisterState& other);
2426 RegisterState& operator=(const RegisterState& other);
2427
2428 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
2429 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
2430 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
2431 void* lr; // Link register (or nullptr on platforms without a link register).
2432 // Callee saved registers (or null if no callee saved registers were stored)
2433 std::unique_ptr<CalleeSavedRegisters> callee_saved;
2434};

3963 // or the object is not extensible.
3964 //
3965 // Returns true on success.

3967 Local<Name> key,

3973 // Implements DefineOwnProperty.
3974 //
3975 // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3976 // for specifying attributes.
3977 //
3978 // Returns true on success.

3982
3983 // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3984 //
3985 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3986 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3987 //
3988 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3989 //
3990 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3991 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3992 //
3993 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3994 //
3995 // Returns true on success.

4510template<typename T>
4511class ReturnValue {
4512 public:
4513 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4514 : value_(that.value_) {
4515 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4516 }
4517 // Local setters
4518 template <typename S>
4519 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4520 template <typename S>
4521 V8_INLINE void Set(const BasicTracedReference<S>& handle);
4522 template <typename S>
4523 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4524 // Fast primitive setters
4525 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4526 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4527 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4528 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4529 // Fast JS primitive setters
4530 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4531 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4532 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4533 // Convenience getter for Isolate
4534 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4535
4536 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4537 template <typename S>
4538 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4539
4540 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4541 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4542 // value.
4543 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4544
4545 private:
4546 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4547 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4548 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4549 template <class F, class G, class H>
4550 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4551 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4552 V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4553 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4554 internal::Address* value_;
4555};

6678struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
6679 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6680 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
6681 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
6682 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query,
6683 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
6684 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
6685 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
6686 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
6687 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6688 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6689 : getter(getter),
6690 setter(setter),
6691 query(query),

7805 size_t bytecode_and_metadata_size_;
7806 size_t external_script_source_size_;
7807
7808 friend class Isolate;

7816struct JitCodeEvent {
7817 enum EventType {
7818 CODE_ADDED,
7819 CODE_MOVED,
7820 CODE_REMOVED,
7821 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7822 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7823 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7824 };
7825 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7826 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7827 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7828 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7829 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7830 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7831
7832 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7833 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7834 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7835 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7836 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7837 // function.
7838 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7839
7840 // Type of event.
7841 EventType type;
7842 CodeType code_type;
7843 // Start of the instructions.
7844 void* code_start;
7845 // Size of the instructions.
7846 size_t code_len;
7847 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7848 Local<UnboundScript> script;
7849 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7850 // code line information which is returned from the
7851 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7852 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7853 void* user_data;
7854
7855 struct name_t {
7856 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7857 // zero-terminated.
7858 const char* str;
7859 // Number of chars in str.
7860 size_t len;
7861 };
7862
7863 struct line_info_t {
7864 // PC offset
7865 size_t offset;
7866 // Code position
7867 size_t pos;
7868 // The position type.
7869 PositionType position_type;
7870 };
7871
7872 struct wasm_source_info_t {
7873 // Source file name.
7874 const char* filename;
7875 // Length of filename.
7876 size_t filename_size;
7877 // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7878 // source file.
7879 const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7880 // Number of entries in the line number table.
7881 size_t line_number_table_size;
7882 };
7883
7884 wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7885
7886 union {
7887 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7888 struct name_t name;
7889
7890 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7891 struct line_info_t line_info;
7892
7893 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7894 void* new_code_start;
7895 };
7896
7897 Isolate* isolate;
7898};
7899
7905enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7906 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7907 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7908 // Throughput may be throttled.
7909 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7910 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7911 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7912 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7913 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7914 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7915 // in this mode.
7916 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7917 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7918 // turn off latency optimizations.
7919 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7920};
7921

7926 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,

7928 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7929};

10166template <class T>
10167class Maybe {
10168 public:
10169 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
10170 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
10171
10175 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
10176
10181 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
10182 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10183 }
10184
10189 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
10190 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
10191 return IsJust();
10192 }
10193
10198 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
10199 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10200 return value_;
10201 }
10202
10207 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
10208 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
10209 }
10210
10211 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10212 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
10213 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
10214 }
10215
10216 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10217 return !operator==(other);
10218 }
10219
10220 private:
10221 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
10222 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
10223
10224 bool has_value_;
10225 T value_;
10226
10227 template <class U>
10228 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10229 template <class U>
10230 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
10231};
10232
10233template <class T>
10234inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
10235 return Maybe<T>();
10236}
10237
10238template <class T>
10239inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
10240 return Maybe<T>(t);
10241}
10242
10243// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
10244template <>
10245class Maybe<void> {
10246 public:
10247 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
10248 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
10249
10250 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10251 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
10252 }
10253
10254 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10255 return !operator==(other);
10256 }
10257
10258 private:
10259 struct JustTag {};
10260
10261 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10262 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10263
10264 bool is_valid_;
10265
10266 template <class U>
10267 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10268 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10269};
10270
10271inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10940// --- Implementation ---
10941
10942template <class T>
10943Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that) {
10944 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10945}
10946
10947template <class T>
10948Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
10949 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10950}
10951
10952template <class T>
10953Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const BasicTracedReference<T>& that) {
10954 return New(isolate, *that);
10955}
10956
10957template <class T>
10958Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10959 if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10960 T* that_ptr = that;
10961 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10962 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10963 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10964}

10967template<class T>
10968template<class S>
10969void Eternal<T>::Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) {
10970 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10971 val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10972 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
10973}
10974
10975template <class T>
10976Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
10977 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
10978 // need to open a handle.
10979 return Local<T>(val_);
10980}

10983template <class T>
10984Local<T> MaybeLocal<T>::ToLocalChecked() {
10985 if (V8_UNLIKELY(val_ == nullptr)) V8::ToLocalEmpty();
10986 return Local<T>(val_);
10987}

10990template <class T>
10991void* WeakCallbackInfo<T>::GetInternalField(int index) const {
10992#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10993 if (index < 0 || index >= kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback) {
10994 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
10995 }
10996#endif
10997 return embedder_fields_[index];
10998}

11001template <class T>
11002T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
11003 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
11004 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
11005 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
11006 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
11007 p));
11008}

11011template <class T, class M>
11012template <class S, class M2>
11013void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
11014 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11015 this->Reset();
11016 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
11017 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
11018 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
11019 M::Copy(that, this);
11020}

11022template <class T>
11023bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
11024 using I = internal::Internals;
11025 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
11026 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
11027 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
11028}

11035 val_ = nullptr;
11036}

11060template <class T>
11061template <typename P>
11062V8_INLINE void PersistentBase<T>::SetWeak(
11063 P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
11064 WeakCallbackType type) {
11065 using Callback = WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback;
11066#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
11067#pragma GCC diagnostic push
11068#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-function-type"
11069#endif
11070 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
11071 reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
11072#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
11073#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
11074#endif
11075}

11079 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11080}

11113
11114template <class T>
11115Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
11116 if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
11117 V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
11118 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11119 other.val_ = nullptr;
11120 }
11121}
11122
11123template <class T>
11124template <class S>
11125Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
11126 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11127 if (this != &rhs) {
11128 this->Reset();
11129 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
11130 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
11131 V8::MoveGlobalReference(
11132 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
11133 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11134 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
11135 }
11136 }
11137 return *this;
11138}
11139
11140template <class T>
11141internal::Address* BasicTracedReference<T>::New(
11142 Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot, DestructionMode destruction_mode) {
11143 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
11144 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
11145 return V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
11146 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
11147 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
11148 destruction_mode == kWithDestructor);
11149}
11150
11151void TracedReferenceBase::Reset() {
11152 if (IsEmpty()) return;
11153 V8::DisposeTracedGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_));
11154 SetSlotThreadSafe(nullptr);
11155}

11157v8::Local<v8::Value> TracedReferenceBase::Get(v8::Isolate* isolate) const {
11158 if (IsEmpty()) return Local<Value>();
11159 return Local<Value>::New(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(val_));
11160}

11162V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11163 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11164 v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11165 v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(rhs.val_);
11166 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11167 if (b == nullptr) return false;
11168 return *a == *b;
11169}
11170
11171template <typename U>
11172V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11173 const v8::Local<U>& rhs) {
11174 v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11175 v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(*rhs);
11176 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11177 if (b == nullptr) return false;
11178 return *a == *b;
11179}
11180
11181template <typename U>
11182V8_INLINE bool operator==(const v8::Local<U>& lhs,
11183 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11184 return rhs == lhs;
11185}
11186
11187V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11188 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11189 return !(lhs == rhs);
11190}
11191
11192template <typename U>
11193V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11194 const v8::Local<U>& rhs) {
11195 return !(lhs == rhs);
11196}

11198template <typename U>
11199V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const v8::Local<U>& lhs,
11200 const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11201 return !(rhs == lhs);
11202}

11364template<typename T>
11365void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
11366 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Number>::value, "type check");
11367 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11368}
11369
11370template<typename T>
11371void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11372 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11373 using I = internal::Internals;
11374 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11375 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11376 return;
11377 }
11378 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11379}
11380
11381template<typename T>
11382void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11383 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11384 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11385 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11386 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11387 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11388 return;
11389 }
11390 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11391}
11392
11393template<typename T>
11394void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11395 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11396 using I = internal::Internals;
11397 int root_index;
11398 if (value) {
11399 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11400 } else {
11401 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11402 }
11403 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11404}
11405
11406template<typename T>
11407void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11408 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11409 using I = internal::Internals;
11410 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11411}
11412
11413template<typename T>
11414void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11415 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11416 using I = internal::Internals;
11417 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11418}
11419
11420template<typename T>
11421void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
11422 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, String>::value, "type check");
11423 using I = internal::Internals;
11424 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11425}
11426
11427template <typename T>
11428Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11429 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11430 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11431}
11432
11433template <typename T>
11434Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11435 using I = internal::Internals;
11436 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11437 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11438 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11439}

11445}

11447template <typename T>
11448internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
11449 // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
11450 return value_[-1];

11459template<typename T>
11460Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
11461 // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11462 if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11463 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ + i));
11464}

11471}

11655
11656Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11657#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11658 using A = internal::Address;
11659 using I = internal::Internals;
11660 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11661 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11662 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11663 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11664 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11665 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11666 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11667 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11668 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11669#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11670 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11671 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11672 value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11673#endif
11674 internal::Isolate* isolate =
11675 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11676 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11677 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11678 }
11679#endif
11680 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11681}
11682
11683
11684void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11685#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11686 using A = internal::Address;
11687 using I = internal::Internals;
11688 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11689 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11690 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11691 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11692 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11693 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11694 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11695 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11696#ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
11697 offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
11698#endif
11699 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11700 A value = I::ReadExternalPointerField(
11701 isolate, obj, offset, internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag);
11702 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
11703 }
11704#endif
11705 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11706}

11723
11724String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11725 using A = internal::Address;
11726 using I = internal::Internals;
11727 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11728
11729 ExternalStringResource* result;
11730 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11731 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11732 A value =
11733 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11734 internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11735 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11736 } else {
11737 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11738 }
11739#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11740 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11741#endif
11742 return result;
11743}
11744
11745
11746String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11747 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11748 using A = internal::Address;
11749 using I = internal::Internals;
11750 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11751 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11752 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11753 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11754 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11755 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11756 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11757 A value =
11758 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11759 internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11760 resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11761 } else {
11762 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11763 }
11764#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11765 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11766#endif
11767 return resource;
11768}

11779bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11780 using A = internal::Address;
11781 using I = internal::Internals;
11782 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11783 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11784 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11785 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11786}

11813
11814bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11815 using A = internal::Address;
11816 using I = internal::Internals;
11817 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11818 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11819 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11820 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11821 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11822}

12300
12301Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
12302#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12303 using A = internal::Address;
12304 using I = internal::Internals;
12305 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12306 A embedder_data =
12307 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12308 int value_offset =
12309 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12310 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12311#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
12312 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
12313 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
12314 value =
12315 I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
12316#endif
12317 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
12318 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
12319 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
12320 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
12321#else
12322 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
12323#endif
12324}
12325
12326
12327void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
12328#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12329 using A = internal::Address;
12330 using I = internal::Internals;
12331 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12332 A embedder_data =
12333 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12334 int value_offset =
12335 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12336#ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
12337 value_offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
12338#endif
12339 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(ctx);
12340 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(
12341 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, embedder_data, value_offset,
12342 internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag));
12343#else
12344 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12345#endif
12346}
12347
12348template <class T>
12349MaybeLocal<T> Context::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index) {
12350 T* data = reinterpret_cast<T*>(GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(index));
12351 if (data) internal::PerformCastCheck(data);
12352 return Local<T>(data);
12353}
12354
12355template <class T>
12356size_t SnapshotCreator::AddData(Local<Context> context, Local<T> object) {
12357 T* object_ptr = *object;
12358 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(object_ptr);
12359 return AddData(context, *p);
12360}
12361
12362template <class T>
12363size_t SnapshotCreator::AddData(Local<T> object) {
12364 T* object_ptr = *object;
12365 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(object_ptr);
12366 return AddData(*p);
12367}
